## Outputs

On success, POSTs the enriched event to `AGENT_{{N_NEXT}}_ENDPOINT` with header
`X-Agent{{N}}-Token: $AGENT_{{N_NEXT}}_SECRET`.

If {{NAME}} is a terminal agent (no forward), delete the outbound block in
`main.py` and document the side effect here (SNOW write, Redis update, etc.).

## Work-note format

Per §4.6 of the repo `CLAUDE.md`, every agent that runs after the INC exists
posts an attributed work note. Use this body:

```
=== {{NAME_UPPER}} — Agent {{N}} ===
Timestamp : <ISO-8601>
Status    : <success | degraded | failed>
Duration  : <ms>
Pipeline  : <pipeline_run_id>

<stage-specific body — fill in>
```

## Environment variables

| Variable | Required | Notes |
|----------|----------|-------|
| `AGENT_{{N}}_PORT`            | yes | `{{PORT}}` |
| `AGENT_{{N}}_SHARED_SECRET`   | yes | inbound secret; must match Agent {{N_PREV}}'s `AGENT_{{N}}_SECRET` |
| `AGENT_{{N_NEXT}}_SECRET`     | yes | outbound secret; must match Agent {{N_NEXT}}'s `AGENT_{{N_NEXT}}_SHARED_SECRET` |
| `AGENT_{{N_NEXT}}_ENDPOINT`   | no  | defaults to `http://agent-{{N_NEXT}}:{{PORT_NEXT}}/intake/...` |
| `REDIS_URL`                   | yes | inherited from `x-common-env` |
| `DATABASE_URL`                | yes | inherited from `x-common-env` |

## Failure modes

| Condition | Behaviour |
|-----------|-----------|
| Inbound auth fails | `401` — Agent {{N_PREV}} retries with backoff then DLQs |
| Downstream agent unreachable | retry → DLQ; pipeline halts unless this agent is non-blocking |
| External API timeout | TODO: define soft-fail vs hard-fail per §10.2 |

